<h1>Club Record Award Conditions</h1>

<ul>
    <li>
        Club Records can only be awarded for performances in official competitions, not club sessions.
        <br/>
        Scores are taken from the final scores provided by the organisers.
        The archer must be identified with an ICAC affiliation on the official results, but does not have to have
        attended the competition as part of a club group.
        <br/>
        Team records can only be achieved where the team total result is specifically published by the organisers.
        <br/>
        &nbsp;
    </li>

    <li>
        If an archer shoots a score in a category for which there is no existing Club Record, then a minimum standard
        must be exceeded for the score acknowledged as a Club Record (and Record Breaker badge awarded).
