    </li>
    <li>
        Seniors cannot hold Novice Club Records, but Novices can hold Senior (Open) Club Records.
        <br/>
        &nbsp;
    </li>
    <li>
        If, during a single session, two (or more) archers
        <ul>
            <li>surpass the same existing Club Record, then both (all) are awarded the Record Breaker badge; the
                high-scorer becomes the new Record Holder.
            </li>
            <li>record a suitable score for a category with no existing Club Record, then only the high-scorer is
                awarded the Record Breaker badge and is the new Record Holder.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        In competitions with multiple sessions, a new Club Record is deemed to stand at the end of the session in which it was shot.
        <br/>
        If an archer shoots a “double” round on a single day, then only the first round may be considered for a Club Record for that
        (single) round
    </li>
</ul>

